<TITLE> Banned Asif can play in club cricket event </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 KARACHI, Sep 27 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Pakistan paceman Mohammad Asif has been given permission to play in a private club tournament although he remains suspended after testing positive for the steroid nandrolone in the Indian Premier League (IPL). A Pakistan Cricket Board spokesman said the ban applied only to events organised by the board. Asif is due to plead his case before the IPL's drugs inquiry tribunal
